organic_results.title: The collegiate scholar: Education for elite status
organic_results.snippet: Evidence from a longitudinal study at a public university shows that collegiate scholars, who combine a strong commitment to academic pursuits with an active involvement in college social and extracurricular life, constitute a discernible subculture on the college campus in terms of its constituency, shared experiences, and goals. It is a subculture steeped in the elite tradition that the purpose of college is to provide a well-rounded undergraduate experience which will prepare the student for a future leadership role in the community or …
